# TypeScript Frontend Rules

## Tauri IPC

- Import `invoke` from `@tauri-apps/api/core` for all backend calls
- Define typed interfaces for every invoke call's arguments and return type
- Never call localhost/fetch for backend communication — always use Tauri invoke
- Handle invoke errors gracefully with user-friendly messages

```typescript
// Good: typed invoke
interface BalanceResponse {
  balance: string;
  chain_id: number;
}

const balance = await invoke<BalanceResponse>("get_balance", {
  chainId: 1,
  address: "0x...",
});
```

## React Patterns

- Functional components only
- Use custom hooks for shared logic (prefix with `use`)
- Zustand for UI state, TanStack Query for async/server state
- Never store sensitive data (keys, balances with full precision) in React state
- Use Tauri event listeners (`listen` from `@tauri-apps/api/event`) for real-time updates from Rust

## TypeScript

- No `any` — use `unknown` with type guards, or proper generics
- No unused variables or parameters (tsconfig enforces)
- Prefer `const` always; never use `var`
- Use discriminated unions for state machines (loading/error/success)

```typescript
// Good: discriminated union
type FetchState<T> =
  | { status: "idle" }
  | { status: "loading" }
  | { status: "error"; error: string }
  | { status: "success"; data: T };
```

## Security in Frontend

- Never perform cryptographic operations in TypeScript — delegate to Rust
- Sanitize all user inputs before sending to Rust backend
- Do not render raw/unsanitized HTML — use React's built-in JSX escaping
- Validate wallet addresses client-side before invoking backend
- No dynamic code evaluation of any kind (no eval, no dynamic function constructors)

## Styling

- Dark theme with purple accent (#8b5cf6)
- Use shadcn/ui components as the base
- TailwindCSS for layout and utilities
- Framer Motion for animations
- JetBrains Mono for numbers, addresses, hashes
- Skeleton loaders, not spinners
